WEBVTT

1
00:01:04.424 --> 00:01:05.676
Huh?

2
00:01:21.358 --> 00:01:23.907
Kenji. Kenji.
Aah!


3
00:01:24.111 --> 00:01:29.459
I'm paying you to clean the floors,
not stare off into space.


4
00:01:29.658 --> 00:01:33.708
I am sorry, Takagawa san,
but I got distracted.


5
00:01:35.122 --> 00:01:41.095
Sadly, that is why no one comes
to the museum anymore.


6
00:01:42.045 --> 00:01:44.673
Too many distractions.
No discipline.


7
00:01:44.881 --> 00:01:48.135
No respect for the old ways.

8
00:01:48.343 --> 00:01:50.345
Come with me. I will show you.

9
00:01:50.554 --> 00:01:53.103
But I saw...

10
00:02:05.694 --> 00:02:10.916
Behold, the Black Samurai.

11
00:02:16.037 --> 00:02:19.041
The Black Samurai.

12
00:02:19.249 --> 00:02:21.502
Never heard of him.

13
00:02:21.710 --> 00:02:24.964
The most fearsome warlord
in the history of Japan.


14
00:02:25.172 --> 00:02:28.176
Do you see what I am
getting at, Kenji?


15
00:02:29.176 --> 00:02:30.223
Uh...

16
00:02:30.427 --> 00:02:32.350
Yes, Takagawa san.

17
00:02:32.554 --> 00:02:34.602
You want me to mop in here.

18
00:02:34.806 --> 00:02:40.404
No, that this exhibit
could save the museum.


19
00:02:49.696 --> 00:02:51.198
What is happening?

20
00:03:15.138 --> 00:03:16.936
I live.

21
00:03:17.140 --> 00:03:19.768
Kenji, do something.

22
00:03:19.976 --> 00:03:21.273
<i>Bonsai!</i>

23
00:03:24.856 --> 00:03:26.324
Uh?

24
00:03:46.211 --> 00:03:51.638
The ghost of the Black Samurai
has returned.


25
00:05:12.923 --> 00:05:15.301
<i>Welcome to Shibuya Station.</i>

26
00:05:15.508 --> 00:05:17.761
<i>Now arriving on Track 5.</i>

27
00:05:19.387 --> 00:05:21.230
<i>Bye-bye.</i>

28
00:05:49.167 --> 00:05:51.716
Wow, we made it, gang.

29
00:05:51.920 --> 00:05:53.217
Shibuya Station.

30
00:05:53.421 --> 00:05:56.220
The most popular meeting
place in all of Tokyo.


31
00:05:56.424 --> 00:05:57.767
And I can see why.

32
00:05:57.968 --> 00:06:00.346
Everyone in Japan
is already here.


33
00:06:01.096 --> 00:06:02.598
But, like, wouldn't you know it?

34
00:06:02.806 --> 00:06:05.685
We're all out of Scooby Snacks.

35
00:06:19.614 --> 00:06:22.788
Scooby Snacks. 
Scooby Snacks.

36
00:06:22.993 --> 00:06:25.746
Way to go, Scoob.
A Scooby Snack vending machine.


37
00:06:27.205 --> 00:06:28.923
Like, it's the wave
of the future.


38
00:06:34.713 --> 00:06:37.011
Hey, I've got a text
message from Miyumi.


39
00:06:37.215 --> 00:06:40.845
She says, "Meet me at
the statue of Hachiko."


40
00:06:41.052 --> 00:06:43.896
Any idea what this Hachiko person
looks like?


41
00:06:44.097 --> 00:06:47.101
Let's see.
Hachiko. Hachiko.


42
00:06:47.308 --> 00:06:49.276
Hachiko. Take a picture.

43
00:06:53.440 --> 00:06:55.568
Hachiko.

44
00:06:56.735 --> 00:06:58.328
Like, check it out, Scoob.

45
00:06:58.528 --> 00:07:00.781
Hachiko's not a person,
he's a pooch.


46
00:07:00.989 --> 00:07:02.036
Here it is.

47
00:07:02.240 --> 00:07:05.790
Hachiko used to greet his master every
day when he came home on the train.


48
00:07:05.994 --> 00:07:07.246
One day his master died...

49
00:07:07.454 --> 00:07:09.673
...and Hachiko
spent the rest of his life...


50
00:07:09.873 --> 00:07:13.093
...waiting at the station
for his master to return.


51
00:07:13.585 --> 00:07:17.135
Wow, sounds like
he was one cool canine.


52
00:07:17.338 --> 00:07:21.559
Heh, heh. Hey, Scoob. Like, maybe
they'll put up a statue of you some day.


53
00:07:21.760 --> 00:07:23.933
Me? Oh, boy.

54
00:07:26.014 --> 00:07:30.064
Ta-da. Bow-wow. Ruff.

55
00:07:30.268 --> 00:07:32.942
Look at Scooby. What a ham.

56
00:07:39.360 --> 00:07:42.739
It's going to take more than that.
Huh?


57
00:07:42.947 --> 00:07:45.370
If you want to have a statue
of your own in Japan...


58
00:07:45.575 --> 00:07:48.249
...you must first become a legend.

59
00:07:48.453 --> 00:07:50.421
Just like Hachiko.

60
00:07:50.622 --> 00:07:53.171
Today, in honor of
his great loyalty...


61
00:07:53.374 --> 00:07:58.676
...his statue serves as a special
place for faithful friends to meet.


62
00:07:58.880 --> 00:08:01.383
Uh, I'm sorry, but have we met?

63
00:08:01.591 --> 00:08:03.434
Huh! You must be Miyumi.

64
00:08:03.635 --> 00:08:06.104
And you are Miss Daphne Blake.

65
00:08:06.304 --> 00:08:09.433
I have heard all about you
and the Scooby gang.


66
00:08:09.641 --> 00:08:11.109
What do you know, Scoob?

67
00:08:11.309 --> 00:08:14.859
Looks like our
reputation precedes us.


68
00:08:15.105 --> 00:08:17.449
Like, I hope that's a good thing.

69
00:08:17.649 --> 00:08:20.027
Heh-heh-heh.
Of course it is.


70
00:08:20.235 --> 00:08:21.657
Can I tell you a secret?

71
00:08:21.861 --> 00:08:25.786
I sometimes wish I could be a
member of the Scooby gang too.


72
00:08:25.990 --> 00:08:27.082
Like, tell you what.

73
00:08:27.283 --> 00:08:31.538
Next time there's a gruesome ghost up
in our grill, you've got first dibs.


74
00:08:31.746 --> 00:08:33.623
Uh-huh.

75
00:08:33.832 --> 00:08:35.505
Hey, don't worry, guys.

76
00:08:35.708 --> 00:08:38.052
We're not here to solve
any mysteries this time.


77
00:08:38.253 --> 00:08:41.974
We're here to watch Daphne compete
in the big martial-arts competition.


78
00:08:42.173 --> 00:08:44.972
I'm so honored
to be invited to the tournament.


79
00:08:45.176 --> 00:08:46.598
And so should you be.

80
00:08:46.803 --> 00:08:51.650
Miss Mirimoto runs the most exclusive
martial-arts academy in all the world.


81
00:08:51.850 --> 00:08:55.229
Only the most exemplary students
are accepted by her.


82
00:08:55.436 --> 00:08:59.566
But first, you must survive
the tournament.


83
00:09:01.025 --> 00:09:03.119
Survive?

84
00:09:03.862 --> 00:09:07.992
Oh, I'm sorry. Did I say "survive"?
Ha, ha. I meant "win."


85
00:09:08.199 --> 00:09:10.247
First, you must win
the tournament.


86
00:09:25.425 --> 00:09:27.098
Wow, what a sweet ride.

87
00:09:27.302 --> 00:09:30.476
All it needs
is a groovy green paint job.


88
00:09:30.680 --> 00:09:32.557
Uh, not quite, Freddy.

89
00:09:32.765 --> 00:09:34.813
I can think of one
more thing it needs.


90
00:09:35.018 --> 00:09:37.396
Like, how about a pilot?

91
00:09:37.604 --> 00:09:40.323
Huh?
Don't worry. We're perfectly safe.


92
00:09:40.523 --> 00:09:46.075
The hover jet is the world's first
fully functioning robotic plane.


93
00:09:46.279 --> 00:09:47.622
That's amazing.

94
00:09:47.822 --> 00:09:49.870
I've studied mechanical
engineering...


95
00:09:50.074 --> 00:09:52.497
...but I've never heard
of anything this advanced.


96
00:09:52.702 --> 00:09:55.376
Here in Japan, technology is
taking over everything...


97
00:09:55.580 --> 00:09:59.130
...while many of the old
traditions are fading away.


98
00:10:21.105 --> 00:10:25.656
Please, Miss Mirimoto,
you must believe me.


99
00:10:25.860 --> 00:10:29.080
The ghost of the Black Samurai
has returned.


100
00:10:29.280 --> 00:10:33.035
Soon, he will come
for the Destiny Scroll.


101
00:10:36.287 --> 00:10:40.258
A very entertaining story,
Mr. Takagawa.


102
00:10:40.458 --> 00:10:45.589
I am sure that it will bring many
new visitors to see your exhibit.


103
00:10:45.797 --> 00:10:50.098
Now, as you can see, our grand
tournament is about to begin.


104
00:10:50.301 --> 00:10:53.976
We would be most pleased
to have you join us.


105
00:10:54.180 --> 00:11:01.109
Sojo, please show our
honored guest to his seat.


106
00:11:01.312 --> 00:11:02.814
You must listen.

107
00:11:04.941 --> 00:11:07.285
The scroll...

108
00:11:07.735 --> 00:11:11.035
...must be protected.

109
00:11:11.239 --> 00:11:13.583
I can assure you, Mr. Takagawa...

110
00:11:13.783 --> 00:11:15.410
...ghost or no ghost...

111
00:11:15.618 --> 00:11:20.715
...the Destiny Scroll will be
quite safe behind these walls.


112
00:11:20.915 --> 00:11:24.089
If you say so.

113
00:11:24.627 --> 00:11:27.426
Sojo. Release him.

114
00:11:30.967 --> 00:11:33.345
You must forgive poor Sojo.

115
00:11:33.553 --> 00:11:35.806
He does only as he is told.

116
00:11:36.014 --> 00:11:39.393
His loyalty to me
is unquestioned.


117
00:11:42.103 --> 00:11:43.480
The plane.

118
00:11:43.688 --> 00:11:45.736
The plane.

119
00:11:52.488 --> 00:11:56.038
Ah, the last of our
guests to arrive.


120
00:11:56.242 --> 00:11:58.961
Have them report
to the staging ground immediately.


121
00:11:59.162 --> 00:12:02.257
We shall have a demonstration.

122
00:12:09.547 --> 00:12:12.391
Wow, what a beautiful airport.

123
00:12:12.592 --> 00:12:14.720
It's not an airport, Freddy.

124
00:12:14.927 --> 00:12:17.771
This is a traditional
Japanese garden.


125
00:12:20.892 --> 00:12:24.522
Can't you just feel the peace
and tranquility?


126
00:12:28.900 --> 00:12:30.652
Oh, yeah.

127
00:12:30.860 --> 00:12:34.990
Scoob, old buddy, like, from here
on out, no matter what happens...


128
00:12:35.198 --> 00:12:37.951
...I'm just gonna
go with the flow.


129
00:12:38.159 --> 00:12:41.333
Go with the flow.

130
00:12:41.537 --> 00:12:44.006
All must Wear uniform.

131
00:12:44.207 --> 00:12:48.178
Gulp! Like, my go-with-the-flow
just got up and went.


132
00:12:48.377 --> 00:12:49.845
Zoinks!

133
00:12:56.719 --> 00:12:59.017
No, Sojo. Bad, Sojo.

134
00:12:59.222 --> 00:13:02.066
Not them. Her.

135
00:13:02.266 --> 00:13:04.735
All must Wear uniform.

136
00:13:04.936 --> 00:13:06.688
Hyah!
Aah!


137
00:13:10.233 --> 00:13:13.908
Sorry, Sojo, but I handle
my own wardrobe.


138
00:13:19.242 --> 00:13:21.210
Ha-ha-ha. Check it out, Scoob.

139
00:13:21.411 --> 00:13:23.288
Like, it's a carnival of karate.

140
00:13:23.496 --> 00:13:25.169
Ooh! Uh-huh.

141
00:13:25.373 --> 00:13:27.967
The competition this
year is fierce.


142
00:13:28.167 --> 00:13:32.718
That's Kerry Kilpatrick,
the Irish national champion.


143
00:13:34.674 --> 00:13:37.678
He's a two-fisted
demolition dynamo.


144
00:13:38.469 --> 00:13:40.517
- Hyah!
- Sapphire Sonja.


145
00:13:40.721 --> 00:13:45.227
The only thing deadlier than
her kick is her beauty.


146
00:13:45.893 --> 00:13:47.566
- Rah!
- Zoinks!


147
00:13:47.770 --> 00:13:51.070
And that's Japan's own
Mad Dog Masimoto.


148
00:13:51.274 --> 00:13:53.151
A favorite to win this year.

149
00:13:53.359 --> 00:13:56.579
Once he's off his leash,
you're really in the doghouse.


150
00:14:02.201 --> 00:14:03.453
Huh!

151
00:14:17.717 --> 00:14:18.809
Gee whiz.

152
00:14:19.010 --> 00:14:21.980
Like, talk about a creep
with a canine complex.


153
00:14:22.180 --> 00:14:23.227
Yeah.

154
00:14:29.562 --> 00:14:32.486
Most honored participants...

155
00:14:32.690 --> 00:14:37.912
...welcome to Mirimoto Academy's
Tournament of Champions.


156
00:14:38.112 --> 00:14:40.831
The finest martial artists
in all the world...


157
00:14:41.032 --> 00:14:45.583
...have gathered here today
for one single purpose:


158
00:14:45.786 --> 00:14:49.541
to prove that they are the best.

159
00:14:52.001 --> 00:14:53.924
By this time tomorrow...

160
00:14:54.128 --> 00:14:59.726
...most of you will be sent home
in humiliating defeat.


161
00:15:03.221 --> 00:15:04.848
But there is one among you...

162
00:15:05.056 --> 00:15:09.027
...who has already displayed
the heart of a champion.


163
00:15:09.227 --> 00:15:11.855
Miss Daphne Blake?

164
00:15:14.524 --> 00:15:16.242
Um, over here.

165
00:15:16.442 --> 00:15:17.989
Hello.

166
00:15:18.194 --> 00:15:19.787
Can this be?

167
00:15:19.987 --> 00:15:21.785
The tournament has
not yet begun...


168
00:15:21.989 --> 00:15:26.335
...and already you have defeated
the mighty Sojo.


169
00:15:26.536 --> 00:15:29.915
I didn't mean to.
It's just that-- Eh--


170
00:15:30.122 --> 00:15:32.124
This is most impressive.

171
00:15:32.333 --> 00:15:34.085
Perhaps you would honor us...

172
00:15:34.293 --> 00:15:38.014
...with a demonstration
of your superior skill.


173
00:15:38.214 --> 00:15:40.342
As in right now?

174
00:15:40.549 --> 00:15:45.225
Your opponent will always attack
when you least expect it.


175
00:16:15.835 --> 00:16:17.087
Huh?

176
00:16:24.719 --> 00:16:28.895
Like, meow. Talk about a
kung-fu cat-fight, ha.


177
00:16:29.098 --> 00:16:31.226
Uh-huh. Meow.

178
00:16:52.705 --> 00:16:55.834
My hair band. I can't see.

179
00:16:58.002 --> 00:17:01.131
Hey, that was a dirty trick.

180
00:17:01.339 --> 00:17:03.592
The first rule of
Mirimoto Academy:


181
00:17:03.799 --> 00:17:04.846
If you want to win...

182
00:17:05.051 --> 00:17:09.147
...you must be willing to do that
which others are not willing to do.


183
00:17:09.847 --> 00:17:12.100
Most impressive, Miss Blake.

184
00:17:12.308 --> 00:17:13.935
You lack proper training...

185
00:17:14.143 --> 00:17:18.819
...but I see in you
much potential.


186
00:17:20.649 --> 00:17:23.744
The tournament begins tomorrow
at sunrise...


187
00:17:23.945 --> 00:17:29.122
...but tonight, a feast has
been prepared in your honor.


188
00:17:32.078 --> 00:17:33.170
Hear that, Scoob?

189
00:17:33.371 --> 00:17:34.873
Like, a feast in our honor.

190
00:17:35.081 --> 00:17:36.458
Oh, boy.

191
00:17:37.917 --> 00:17:41.842
Finally, something
worth fighting for.


192
00:18:10.449 --> 00:18:13.544
Boy, the service here is great...

193
00:18:14.537 --> 00:18:18.292
...but, uh, our waitress
sure could use a suntan.


194
00:18:18.499 --> 00:18:21.594
She's not a waitress, Freddy.
She's a geisha girl.


195
00:18:21.794 --> 00:18:26.265
Geisha, the ancient Japanese tradition
celebrating exquisite beauty.


196
00:18:26.465 --> 00:18:29.264
Speaking of beauty,
check out the buffet table.


197
00:18:29.468 --> 00:18:30.515
Oh, ho, ho!

198
00:18:30.720 --> 00:18:34.600
It's like there's a party in my
stomach and everything's invited.


199
00:18:34.807 --> 00:18:35.854
Yeah.

200
00:18:40.813 --> 00:18:41.939
Hyah!

201
00:18:49.280 --> 00:18:52.625
Ha-ha-ha. Like, you must be
a black belt in kung food.


202
00:18:54.076 --> 00:18:55.123
Yeah.

203
00:18:56.787 --> 00:19:00.917
Forget the karate chop.
Like, check out my karate chomp.


204
00:19:04.920 --> 00:19:06.388
Huh?

205
00:19:07.381 --> 00:19:09.383
Huh! Ninjas!

206
00:19:20.311 --> 00:19:24.737
Wow, real-life ninjas. How cool.

207
00:19:24.940 --> 00:19:27.113
I don't think these guys
are part of the act.


208
00:19:29.111 --> 00:19:30.203
Watch out.

209
00:19:31.947 --> 00:19:33.915
If it's a fight you
be looking for...


210
00:19:34.116 --> 00:19:36.665
...then you've found the bloke
to oblige you.


211
00:19:41.874 --> 00:19:43.171
Out of my way.

212
00:19:43.375 --> 00:19:46.845
Let Sapphire Sonja
show you how to kick it.


213
00:20:00.810 --> 00:20:01.857
Hmm?

214
00:20:17.993 --> 00:20:19.290
We're surrounded.

215
00:20:35.427 --> 00:20:36.474
Who's that?

216
00:20:36.679 --> 00:20:39.478
Gulp! Who cares?
Not me.


217
00:20:41.475 --> 00:20:42.727
Let's get out of here.

218
00:21:49.126 --> 00:21:50.594
Huh?

219
00:21:58.385 --> 00:21:59.807
Huh?

220
00:22:40.177 --> 00:22:41.599
Yipes!

221
00:22:41.804 --> 00:22:44.057
Like, I almost forgot.

222
00:22:44.265 --> 00:22:46.643
We're afraid of heights.

223
00:22:55.943 --> 00:22:58.913
Shaggy, look.

224
00:23:03.409 --> 00:23:05.127
At long last...

225
00:23:05.327 --> 00:23:10.925
...the Destiny Scroll is mine.

226
00:23:13.961 --> 00:23:16.339
Stop, thief.
Huh?


227
00:23:17.756 --> 00:23:20.635
You will not be
allowed to escape.


228
00:23:25.097 --> 00:23:27.225
You are too late.

229
00:23:27.433 --> 00:23:30.277
We shall let steel decide.

230
00:23:46.493 --> 00:23:47.540
Yipes!

231
00:23:59.673 --> 00:24:03.018
The Black Samurai
will live again...


232
00:24:03.218 --> 00:24:05.516
...forever!

233
00:24:12.186 --> 00:24:13.233
So it is true.

234
00:24:13.437 --> 00:24:16.816
The ghost of the Black Samurai
has returned.


235
00:24:17.024 --> 00:24:19.948
Gulp! Ghost?

236
00:24:21.612 --> 00:24:23.205
It just doesn't add up.

237
00:24:23.405 --> 00:24:26.079
The artwork in this collection
must be worth a fortune.


238
00:24:26.283 --> 00:24:29.833
So why go through all that trouble
just to steal one scroll?


239
00:24:30.037 --> 00:24:32.005
Well, gang,
it looks like we've landed...


240
00:24:32.206 --> 00:24:35.335
...smack dab
in the middle of another mystery.


241
00:24:35.542 --> 00:24:38.170
It is no mystery.

242
00:24:39.046 --> 00:24:44.143
The legend of the Black Samurai
has been told for centuries.


243
00:24:44.343 --> 00:24:47.062
May I present
Mr. Takagawa...


244
00:24:47.262 --> 00:24:52.439
...most honored curator from the
Tokyo Museum of Cultural History.


245
00:24:52.935 --> 00:24:54.858
Pleased to meet you,
Mr. Takagawa.


246
00:24:55.062 --> 00:24:56.564
You'll have to excuse us.

247
00:24:56.772 --> 00:24:59.491
We don't really know much
about Japanese folklore.


248
00:24:59.691 --> 00:25:01.739
But ghosts are kind
of our specialty.


249
00:25:01.944 --> 00:25:03.662
Speak for yourself.

250
00:25:03.862 --> 00:25:07.116
My specialty is a triple-decker
Scooby Snack-and-ice-cream...


